Detailed Description

A SubSystem is a singleton that needs to initialize on power up or garbage collect on power down system resources. Derivatives of SubSystem must be instantiated in global scope. The constructor of SubSystem will care that for registering sub-systems in SubSystemManager. On special system events like power up / down according methods will be invoked. Thread context of method invokation is not defined - at method invokation time bigger parts of APOXI might not be initialized. Thus functionality should be limited to thread creation, memory allocation, or internal initialization. Typical examples of sub-systems could be inet (tcp/udp) or Bluetooth.
